I'm going to try to go there again on Saturday. The weather isn't great right now, but it's only Monday.
The difficulties are already starting to show. I will probably have A LOT of trouble getting a medical certificate, due to the FAA's stance on certain medications.
Not impossible, but it will take ENORMOUSLY much time and require A LOT of extra work.
Even though it's discouraging, it's just another problem to solve and, for now, it seems *completely* surmountable. It's just that it will take a lot of time and $$.
In case the challenge I'm facing interests you.
The FAA isn't a fan of ADHD. It doesn't issue a medical certificate if you're undergoing treatment for it.
https://youtu.be/W5JSfq6LLAU?si=xIxPaY8ayqqNSj4c
If ever I have the opportunity to get a personalized registration number, it will FORCIBLY be a variation of N1337_, with the _ corresponding to any available final alphabetical character.
